  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1ae8fea1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Compute Revenue-per-Order Estimate\n",
    "\n",
    "Average order value is derived from `Average Cost for two` (halved, since\n",
    "it represents two people) with some noise."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "294f33e2",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-03-01T18:15:21.607435Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-03-01T18:15:21.607285Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-03-01T18:15:21.699029Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-03-01T18:15:21.697726Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "✅ Avg order value computed\n",
      "   Min: ₹50\n",
      "   Max: ₹575411\n",
      "   Mean: ₹787\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def compute_avg_order_value(row):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Estimate average order value from cost-for-two.\"\"\"\n",
    "    cost_for_two = row[\"Average Cost for two\"]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if cost_for_two <= 0:\n",
    "        # Fallback based on price range\n",
    "        fallback = {1: 200, 2: 500, 3: 1000, 4: 2000}\n",
    "        cost_for_two = fallback.get(row[\"Price range\"], 400)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Single-person order ≈ 55-75% of cost-for-two\n",
    "    avg_order = cost_for_two * np.random.uniform(0.55, 0.75)\n",
    "    return max(avg_order, 50)  # minimum ₹50\n",
    "\n",
    "restaurants[\"avg_order_value\"] = restaurants.apply(compute_avg_order_value, axis=1)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ Avg order value computed\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Min: ₹{restaurants['avg_order_value'].min():.0f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Max: ₹{restaurants['avg_order_value'].max():.0f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"   Mean: ₹{restaurants['avg_order_value'].mean():.0f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d835d0af",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Generate Daily Orders\n",
    "\n",
    "For each restaurant × each day, we simulate:\n",
    "1. **Seasonal factor** – sine-wave monthly trend\n",
    "2. **Day-of-week multiplier** – weekday vs weekend\n",
    "3. **Holiday spike** – 50–100% boost\n",
    "4. **Random noise** – Gaussian perturbation\n",
    "5. **Promotion events** – ~15% of days, with discount impact\n",
    "6. **Revenue** – orders × avg_order_value × (1 − discount)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "3a45dfc2",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-03-01T18:15:21.703238Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-03-01T18:15:21.702851Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-03-01T18:16:25.777042Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-03-01T18:16:25.775839Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
